1. Set Up Your Environment
Install Python
Make sure you have Python installed. You can download it from python.org.

Install Flask
You can install Flask using pip. Open your terminal and run:
pip install Flask

To set up your project structure in Visual Studio Code (VSCode), follow these steps:
Step 1: Open VSCode
Launch Visual Studio Code on your computer.

Running the Application
To start your Flask application, run the following command in the terminal:
python app.py

Exit the Virtual Environment 
Deactivate the Virtual Environment: Type the following command and press Enter:
deactivate

To add a database to your Flask backend, you can use an ORM (Object-Relational Mapping) library like SQLAlchemy, which is commonly used with Flask. 

Step 1: Install SQLAlchemy (in the detect node)
You need to install SQLAlchemy and Flask-SQLAlchemy. You can do this using pip:

pip install Flask-SQLAlchemy

/your_project
│
├── app.py  # Your main Flask application file
│
├── templates/  # Folder for HTML files
│   ├── home.html
│   ├── admin.html
│   ├── login.html
│   ├── signup.html
│   └── user-profile.html
│
└── static/  # Folder for CSS, JS, and other static files
    └── style.css  # Your CSS file (example)
